{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 143955, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Cybersonix", "body": "In warcraft 3 at the end of Night elf campagin were you defend The World Tree, this guy appears. He is one of the attackers that leads undead at you. Probobly the hardest one of the 3 heros that attacks you. Thats why he is probobly the fourth boss.", "date": "2007-08-25T17:00:55-05:00", "rating": 22, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Can be soloed on DK but only if he's alone so he wont get doom debuff, also there's 10min enrage timer so slap some dps gear with your tanking gear and kite him trough every single NPC in that camp.", "creationdate": "2010-09-24T07:36:55-05:00", "id": 183447, "rating": 2, "commentid": 143955, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "608989", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 151383, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "11529", "body": "\"Any attack causes the boss swing timer to reset\" is wrong.\r\n\r\nParries do this. Not autoattack.", "date": "2007-09-10T18:32:43-05:00", "rating": 37, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 155795, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "87230", "body": "While killing Azgalor, make sure you are within 100 yards range from him when he dies, because otherwise you can't loot him.\n\nToday on our kill i was assigned to heal Doomguard tank who has tanking them next to Thrall. When Azgalor was on low HP i got killed by a stray Doomguard. Girdle of Hope dropped, i won the bid, and noticed i couldn't loot him. Really frustrating when it happens.My guild uses FFA loot though, so i don't know if it affects Master Looting as well.", "date": "2007-09-20T17:09:32-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes, it's the same thing with master looting.  [b]Try not to stand too far away if you are in the \"doomguard-camp\" as it can lead to not being able to loot the boss.[/b] This happened to some [u]people who died of Doom[/u] and to some [u]rogues fighting the doomguard[/u] as well.  We tanked Azgalor on Thralls position and set up the doomguard-camp near the tauren warriors. I think standing behind this little beige brick kind of thing is not good. :)", "creationdate": "2008-07-08T04:37:38-05:00", "id": 340808, "rating": 0, "commentid": 155795, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Corbomite", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just make sure you appear on his aggro table. If you don't attack or heal someone close to him before you run off to do your doomguard responsibilities its possible you won't show up on his aggro table and therefore won't be allowed to loot him. Which sucks, because this is the first dude that drops T6 in Hyjal. So yeah, just make sure you attack or heal someone who's being attacked before you run off to tank doomguards or w/e :P", "creationdate": "2008-08-02T10:07:24-05:00", "id": 41770, "rating": 3, "commentid": 155795, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "170065", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It has nothing to do with your relative range to him when he dies. Hashmahalum is correct, get on his aggro table. Should be easy enough since there won't a Doomguard for the first ~40 seconds. Just take a single swing at him if you're the Doomguard tank/his healer and then move out of range.  If it does happen that you're unable to loot, have someone else loot it, then let that person ticket a GM, explain the situation and the GM will transfer the item to its rightful owner.", "creationdate": "2008-09-24T22:59:07-05:00", "id": 47917, "rating": 1, "commentid": 155795, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "207285", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2007-09-20T17:10:51-05:00", 1, "87230"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 155812, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "87237", "body": "Just a helpful tip that my guild has had great experience with:\n\nIf you wear your [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=32649]Medallion of Karabor[/url] (BT attunement key) along with getting Shadow Protection buff you will have a much easier time dealing with the silences, which are in fact shadow spells.\n\nAs the Doom Guard offtank you may want to get a bring Free Action Potions because once you end up tanking two or three of these guys you will be stunned a lot by the War Stomp, making it quite hard to pick up another should one spawn while you are stunned.", "date": "2007-09-20T17:44:19-05:00", "rating": 20, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Doom does not take dura damage.", "creationdate": "2008-10-31T16:15:41-05:00", "id": 53717, "rating": 1, "commentid": 155812, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Yuka2", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-06-07T15:34:00-05:00", 1, "Arideni"]}
