{"commentv2": 1, "number": 29, "id": 1564752, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "547579", "body": "As far as I can tell, he is unsoloable by a hunter.  The pet takes the place as the tank and he will cast Doom on you.  It is impossible to range him without auto-dismissing your pet, and sitting FD while your pet does the work will not beat the enrage.", "date": "2011-11-06T13:52:56-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 30, "id": 1578971, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nobbel", "body": "Here are 2 videos for a guide I made on how to solo Battle for Mount Hyjal.\r\nI use my hunter for the first 3 bosses (Rage Winterchill,Anetheron & Kaz'Rogal) then switch over to my Paladin for the last 2 (Azgalor & Archimonde).\r\nTacs can be used for any group or class. \r\nI hope it helps in whatever you want to get out of the instance.\r\n\r\nPart 1:Rage Winterchill,Anetheron & Kaz'Rogal\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7u6MsZgCJF8&hd=1\r\nPart 2:Azgalor & Archimonde\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yz7QOLIITWI&hd=1", "date": "2011-11-23T06:10:58-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 31, "id": 1584411, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "coops025", "body": "We tried this boss last night:\r\n\r\n85 Pala Tank\r\n85 Hunter (me) Gear average 346\r\n82 Mage (The Mrs) Gear Average 316\r\n\r\nHe seems to target the person with the lowest threat first (uncomfirmed) then the next in line. \r\n\r\nWe nuked him hard, he took  out  the mage, then me (hunter) leaving him with around 20% health left and the tank was not able to keep his hp up throught the rest of the fight and died, even after a lay on hands. \r\n\r\nWe tried to kite him to thrall and the other npc's nearby which really helps.\r\n\r\nWe wiped on about 5% so as long as you can pack enough punch before dieing you should be ok. \r\n\r\nWe also tried letting the mage and tank die on purpose during the last wave of mobs to see if my hunter could solo and have the doom debuff bug, this did'nt work. \r\n\r\nDivine sheild and Iceblock will not remove the doom debuff. \r\n\r\nI even had another idea where i asked the tank to remove Rightous Fury so that i had higher threat than the tank and mage so that i can live to kill him, this worked however the doom debuff killed me, even though i was the last alive (hunter)?\r\n\r\n\r\nSo if you plan getting theT6 gloves you either need to be solo (prefered a hunter which is easy) or you need high enough  dps before you die to finish him.", "date": "2011-11-30T08:50:39-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-11-30T08:57:42-06:00", 4, "coops025"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 32, "id": 1610413, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nobbel", "body": "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u8tsDs1ndoc&hd=1\r\n\r\nA guide on how to solo Battle for Mount Hyjal as a retribution paladin 5/5.\r\nIt took me around 1h and 7 min to complete and I had around 1573g without selling any BoE.\r\n\r\nHope it helps, happy farming.\r\n\r\nNobbel the Noble", "date": "2012-01-12T12:53:13-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "When I read this it totally read out in my head in your voice, lol. I've seen too many of your lore guides on YouTube. Keep up the good work!", "creationdate": "2014-02-08T16:54:10-06:00", "id": 727338, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1610413, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "zknm7", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 33, "id": 1644479, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "demonlock666", "body": "The Current Pit Lord King.\r\nAlthough he didnt die in WoW lore, you do get to kill him in World of Warcraft: The Burning Crusade. It is quite possible he will return in the future WoW expansions as a Raid Boss.", "date": "2012-03-25T11:31:36-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 34, "id": 1672912, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Hairband", "body": "This boss you will engage at Horde Encampment, and he is the 2nd boss (4/5 in all) that you will meet.  The way it works is there are gonna be 2 bosses for each encampment and of course Archimonde is at the Tree of Nordrassil.  It's a long walk if you prematurely head to the Tree of Nordrassil.\r\n\r\nYou will engage him after the waves, for which you will see 2 counters at the top of your UI.  The first counter is the number of mobs in the wave, so each time you kill one you'll see the number go down.  The second counter is the number of total waves, I think it was 8.  The waves consist of Ghouls, Abominations, Necromancers (human male casters), one or two Frost Wyrms and Gargoyles.  Your NPC's help you here.  You do have to run around a lot to see where the mobs are.  Sometimes you get to 1-2 left and you have to scout around to see them.\r\n\r\nWhen you are done killing him, you may now continue to Tyrande and get your special free fall dust, then continue to kill Archimonde.  \r\n\r\nNOTE:  This was a 25 man raid only so I believe at this time you need at least 10 guildies to get the Guild Hyjal Summit achievement.", "date": "2012-06-03T01:07:58-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 35, "id": 1692410, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "littlemac007", "body": "Duoed him as a level 85 Hunter and 85 Warlock. Warlock was tank in Affliction spec. Warlock puts soulstone on hunter and hunter gets warlock aggro and does as much damage as he can before dooms hits. When doom hits you rez with soulstone and fire away again. By the time the second doom hits you he should be about 30% (give or take) the warlock should be able to handle him then with all the self healing spells.", "date": "2012-07-26T16:28:46-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 36, "id": 1696209, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "ImVeryNewHere", "body": "Was able to brute force a kill as Demo Lock on only my second attempt ever. I was in Heroic DS gear along with [item=70142 domain=www]\r\n\r\n- Soulstone yourself\r\n- Use Felguard\r\n- Before you engage setup your teleport half way between the boss and Thrall\r\n- Get aggro with a few spells then run and teleport and get CoE up while running to Thrall\r\n- Pop all cooldowns, then pop Meta\r\n- Pop Doomguard\r\n- Normal DPS rotation\r\n- When you get to about 10% of your health use Soulshatter\r\n- You will have 20 seconds to free cast on the boss before the debuff kills you\r\n- Pop with soulstone right after death, finish boss", "date": "2012-08-05T01:53:10-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 37, "id": 1719929, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "15909", "body": "Soloable as hunter, patch 5.0.4. Recommended spec: BM, because your pet will be on boss at all times, and you won't. Recommended pet: ferocity spirit beast. Spirit Bond is also highly recommended, as well as Glyph of Animal Bond and Glyph of Mending.\r\n\r\nThe trick for this boss is to avoid Doom, which has a range of 100yd, and here is how I have done it a couple of times:\r\n\r\nWhen engaging the boss, have a timer for Doom cooldown (I used default WoW stopwatch), which is 45 seconds. Go full dps for around 20 seconds, then start moving away from the boss, while spamming Hunter's Mark. [b]Pet needs to between you and boss[/b], otherwise it won't work. When you think you are 100yd away, slow down a bit, while still spamming hunter's mark. When you get an error message about target not in line of sight, stop immediately. Your pet should not despawn, because it's around 95-99yd from you, and you should be just over 100yd from the boss. Take note of your surroundings - this will help you find this magic distance again.\r\n\r\nWhen boss casts Doom, reset your timer, if you are using a stopwatch, and engage the boss with full dps again. Move away after 15-35 seconds, whatever you feel comfortable with. Rinse and repeat. If you have Lynx Rush, do not use it - it might mess up your positioning or even despawn your pet, if you are far away. Don't forget to mend your pet if it's health is getting low.\r\n\r\nIf your pet despawns, don't panic. You might still be able to pull it off if you quickly resurrect your pet. If you get Doom, die quickly and run back in as fast as possible. The boss might still be around killing NPCs, giving you a chance for another try without having to kill the undead waves again.", "date": "2012-09-26T09:38:55-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I tried this strategy and found that, interestingly, marker flares also vanish when you move more than 100 yards from them XD. The short version is, I just stood and killed him using whatever CDs i had, finished with 40%hp left, my avg iLvl is 446. Maybe worth keeping a spirit beast out for 40 second, then throw it's HoT on you, dismiss and just kill away :)", "creationdate": "2012-12-31T22:43:51-06:00", "id": 617801, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1719929, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Smokingshrapnel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 38, "id": 1741971, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Rikeus", "body": "As far as I can tell, this guy is impossible to solo regardless of level (I tried as a level 90 mage) thanks to his doom spell. Can't be avoided, can't be removed, can't do &*!@ about it. What a load of !@#$.", "date": "2012-10-15T01:41:31-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 39, "id": 1744249, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "110266", "body": "Level 90:s, listen up!\r\n\r\nDon't be discouraged by comments like Rikeus'. This CAN be downed with brute force. As a level 90 Shaman with somewhat average mop heroic (dungeon - not raid!) gear I was able to kill Azgalor without even breaking the 45 second mark for the first debuff to be cast.\r\n\r\nAll you need is to be able to do 3.7 million damage in 65 seconds (45s first cast + 20 debuff time).   This means you'll need around 55k DPS if I'm not mistaken. I'm quite certain this can be attained by most level 90 damage dealers in decent early MoP gear.\r\n\r\nHave fun and enjoy the loot!", "date": "2012-10-17T17:44:05-05:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This is definitely possible. I just solo'd him as a 475 frost mage. I did 58k dps and killed him in about 70 seconds. I never even saw him cast doom. He may have cast it on my elemental since I wasn't watching it's debuffs closely.", "creationdate": "2012-10-26T14:32:28-05:00", "id": 591270, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1744249, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "806656", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 40, "id": 1767899, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "aphistis", "body": "Easy hunter solo as of 5.0.5.\n\nLevel 90, ilvl 486, Beast Mastery. The burst capacity of BM is what trivializes this fight. It may be possible as Survival, but you're making a lot of unnecessary extra work for yourself. Finally, if you're using a Marksmanship spec in 5.0.x, go change it to BM or SV. Yes, you. Right now.\n\n- Spec your pet for Ferocity, not Tenacity, and spec into Spirit Bond. The extra DPS of Ferocity will help you down the boss, and Tenacity mitigation is way overkill for a Burning Crusade boss at level 90. [b]I recommend a core hound for Ancient Hysteria.[/b] Otherwise, any ferocity pet will suffice.\n- Agility food, flasks, and/or Drums of Forgotten Kings can be used as needed to boost your DPS output.\n\n\n- When Azgalor appears, apply Hunter's Mark from a distance to save yourself a GCD.\n- Once he's in range, pre-potion, send in your pet, and cut loose with everything you've got: Ancient Hysteria, Bestial Wrath, Stampede, Lynx Rush, Dire Beast, agility potion, Serpent Sting, Rapid Fire.\n- Hit Readiness, and do it all over again. The boss should be dead by the time you reach the end of your cooldowns.\n- Hopefully your DPS will be high enough that Azgalor dies before casting Doom. If he does, though, KEEP GOING! You still have 20 seconds from the time of the cast to finish him off, which should be ample time to finish him off. If you die after the boss goes down, he stays dead and you can continue.\n\n- Kill, loot, onward to Nordrassil and Archimonde!", "date": "2012-11-25T19:48:03-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You were right, but glad I read here. I didn't know about the Doom and spent so much time blowing kisses to his plump, adorable dumpling self and flirting with him that I died to Doom my first try. (SV can do it btw, I just have to stop being distracted by his sexiness.)", "creationdate": "2012-12-24T23:35:16-06:00", "id": 615538, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1767899, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Aliandrin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This is the best strat for solo hunter. I used core hound pet like he said, popped Ancient Hysteria, then blew my CD's. Turn off growl!!! It took all of 41 seconds to down him. 484 BM Hunter, 104k DPS is what I pulled for that fight.", "creationdate": "2012-12-28T00:45:52-06:00", "id": 616484, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1767899, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ental", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Even a lower geared hunter can solo this as i did. Just keep your pet out for 40 seconds or so, use a corehound for extra damage, or spirit beast to throw a HoT on yourself, then dismiss it (or accidentally despawn it XD) and finish him yourself. As a avg iLvl 446 BM hunter i finished with 40% HP left using one health pot. He doesn't hit hard enough on mail to win the DPS race, just use CDs, disengage out of the fire rain, he will likely die before you do :)", "creationdate": "2012-12-31T23:02:00-06:00", "id": 617806, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1767899, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Smokingshrapnel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-11-25T19:49:21-06:00", 2, "aphistis"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 41, "id": 1777263, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Karadine", "body": "For soloing warlocks and hunters (@90), very simple.  Use a DPS pet and turn off Growl/Threatening Presence so that -you- are the tank.  He'll never cast [spell=31347] on you if you are top on threat. He does use a fairly long silence ([spell=31344]) and casts [spell=31340] which you'll probably want to get out of, but overall a very easy fight as long as you avoid Doom.", "date": "2012-12-07T15:47:30-06:00", "rating": 15, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-12-07T15:51:14-06:00", 2, "Karadine"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 42, "id": 1795054, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "pepeu", "body": "He wont cast Doom on you if you're at top of threat. So, as a level 90 frost mage I managed to solo this with ease, after a little trial and error. I go blasting, popping all CD:s at the start, and then after 40 seconds or so, I dismiss my water elemental so he's only fighting me. One evocation in the midst of the fight to keep my health up. Pew pew and loot loot! :O)", "date": "2013-01-08T20:39:07-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 43, "id": 1817235, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "KillMaster", "body": "Soloed on 25man difficulty as 88lvl crap geared, 20k DPS Demo lock, taking debuff only when pet aggroed boss. Downed him uder 50% before firs debuff.", "date": "2013-02-23T05:01:42-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "lol I'll give you 2 ups just bc whoever gave you the downs did not put a reason. 20k is pretty crap dps for destro. But it is better than saying you did it on a level 90 shammy.", "creationdate": "2015-02-02T15:01:16-06:00", "id": 835669, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1817235, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "gbalkam", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 44, "id": 1839618, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "rcingnoob", "body": "Trial and error proved useful in this fight.\r\nDoom, which is cast on someone who is not holding agro on the boss will instantly die after 20 seconds.\r\n\r\nAs a hunter and on my first time of doing this raid solo, send my pet in with misdirect was a terrible mistake.\r\nAbout 1.5m hp down then I got the Doom debuff and died shortly after.\r\n\r\nTried again with my pet still out, but not using misdirect. I was only taking about 5k damage per hit and my Spirit Bond was able to heal me between each hit making this a fairly easy boss.\r\n\r\nDon't do what I did and not check abilitys before fighting this boss. But if you looking here it's probably already too late. Lol", "date": "2013-04-06T02:47:32-05:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 45, "id": 1878456, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1133292", "body": "Azgolar is actually easier to solo rather than duo as he never casts mark of doom on the person aggroing him. So he will only mark your friend who is just dpsing/healing. Same thing rings true of Archimonde and his air burst.", "date": "2013-07-19T04:49:32-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
